%% Training Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Client
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Controller as Training Operator Controller<br/>(opendatahub namespace)
    participant Pods as Worker Pods<br/>(user namespace)
    participant HeadlessSvc as Headless Service<br/>(DNS discovery)
    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>(openshift-monitoring)

    Note over User,Prometheus: Flow 1: Training Job Submission

    User->>K8sAPI: POST PyTorchJob/TFJob/etc CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / Client Cert
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-*<br/>443->9443/TCP, TLS (self-signed)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (allow/deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR Created / Rejected

    Note over Controller,Pods: Flow 2: Controller Reconciliation

    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event (new CR detected)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create worker Pods<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create headless Service<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy (PyTorch only)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create HPA (elastic PyTorch only)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA Token

    Note over Pods,HeadlessSvc: Flow 3: Distributed Training Execution

    Pods->>HeadlessSvc: DNS lookup for peer pods
    HeadlessSvc-->>Pods: Pod IP addresses
    Pods->>Pods: Inter-worker communication<br/>framework-specific ports, TCP, plaintext<br/>(NetworkPolicy: same-job pods only)

    Note over Prometheus,Controller: Flow 4: Metrics Collection

    Prometheus->>Controller: GET /metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP plaintext<br/>(PodMonitor)
